h 3-5 leaflets that are ovate, pointed and serrated. The plant produces white, fragrant flowers in a compound corymb, with 5 petals and 5 stamens, in late spring to early summer. The flowers are followed by aggregate fruits (synconia), consisting of multiple drupes (drupelets), which are red to purple when mature. The variety is found in China and other parts of Asia."}